    • Method Detail

      • availableTailOp

        Iterator availableTailOp()
        Opportunity for a Striterator to provide a "tail iterator" to shorten the call stack. For example, an Appenderator would return the second iterator if current. Or an Expanderator the child iterator if there were no more source objects.
        Returns:
        a tail optimizing iterator if possible
